\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department maintains a structured workforce framework to ensure operational continuity,
 clear authority boundaries,
 and defensible competency standards across all service delivery and governance functions.
 This framework aligns role definitions with industry workforce standards and maps competency requirements to the 
\series bold
Skills,
 Tasks,
 Abilities,
 and Knowledge (STAK)
\series default
 matrix maintained in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Role Tier Structure and Access Eligibility
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department is organized into hierarchical role tiers to ensure operational clarity,
 escalation discipline,
 and professional development.
 Role tiers L0 through L5 correspond directly to the roles defined in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Screening Requirements
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall not assign any individual,
 including contractors and temporary personnel,
 to a role above Trainee (Tier L0) until the individual has successfully completed the background screening required for the applicable access classification as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Personnel Security and Background Screening Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Rescreening
\series default
:
 Personnel with access to Criminal Justice Information (CJI) shall undergo rescreening at least once every five (5) years in accordance with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section PS-3 (Personnel Screening).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Advancement
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall verify that an individual's background screening adjudication remains current and appropriate for the target tier's access classification before approving advancement between tiers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 Assignment to Tier L0 (Trainee) does not exempt personnel from screening requirements applicable to the access they will receive.
 No individual shall be granted logical or physical access beyond what the individual's adjudicated access classification permits under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Competency Maintenance
\series default
:
 Assignment to Tier L3 (Administrator) and above shall be contingent upon maintaining all requirements designated as mandatory in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 including required certifications and renewals where specified.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lapse
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall immediately suspend the affected individual's administrative privileges and remove the individual from unsupervised Tier L3+ duties upon discovery of a lapse in any mandatory requirement (e.g.,
 expiration,
 revocation,
 or failure to maintain renewal status).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Reassignment
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall temporarily reassign the affected individual to Tier L2 (Support Specialist) duties or lower until the requirement is reinstated or a written exception is approved under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Documentation
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall document all privilege suspensions,
 exceptions,
 and reinstatements in the Department's system of record and shall manage non-compliance under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tier Definitions
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Director Level (Tier L5)
\series default
:
 Provides strategic leadership,
 governance,
 and oversight.
 Focus is on Strategy and Risk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant Director Level (Tier L4)
\series default
:
 Manages operations and workforce development.
 Focus is on Operations and Governance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Administrator Level (Tier L3)
\series default
:
