 security controls,
 and engineering.
 Focus is on Stability and Security.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Support Specialist Level (Tier L2)
\series default
:
 Provides front-line support and resolution.
 Focus is on Service and Resolution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Administrative Assistant Level (Tier L1)
\series default
:
 Provides triage and logistics.
 Focus is on Process and Logistics.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Trainee Level (Tier L0)
\series default
:
 Focus is on Learning and Assimilation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Role Definitions and Duties
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The following roles define the operational and governance structure of the Information Operations Department.
 The IT Director shall ensure that formal County position descriptions align with these definitions and with the competencies defined in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 The IT Director is the senior technology authority,
 reporting to the County Manager,
 with statutory responsibilities established under NRS 242.171.
 The IT Director shall:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Strategic Planning
\series default
:
 Develop and drive IT strategy aligned with Elko County's statutory duties and public service objectives.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Governance
\series default
:
 Establish and maintain the Information Operations Policy Manual,
 ensuring compliance with Federal,
 State,
 and Local mandates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Leadership
\series default
:
 Serve as the designated Chief Information Security Officer (CISO) function,
 holding ultimate accountability for the County's cybersecurity posture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Financial Management
\series default
:
 Manage the departmental budget,
 capital improvement plans (CIP),
 and procurement contracts.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director serves as the operational executive and deputizes for the IT Director.
 The Assistant IT Director shall:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operations Management
\series default
:
 Oversee daily IT service delivery,
 ensuring adherence to Service Level Agreements (SLAs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Workforce Development
\series default
:
 Manage staffing,
 performance evaluations,
 and the execution of role-based technical training and exercises assigned under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Project Governance
\series default
:
 Lead the IT project portfolio to ensure initiatives are delivered on time,
 within scope,
 and on budget.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Deputization
\series default
:
 Assume decision-making authority in the IT Director's absence only to the extent formally delegated under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
