\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Advancement Pathways
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall evaluate advancement candidates based on demonstrated competency mastery,
 certification acquisition,
 and adherence to the standards defined in this policy.
 Tenure alone shall not constitute grounds for promotion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Criteria
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall base advancement decisions on technical competency as measured against 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the individual's security compliance history (e.g.,
 adherence to policies,
 absence of unresolved disciplinary actions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Competency Verification
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify that the candidate meets all mandatory STAK requirements for the target tier prior to the IT Director's advancement decision.
\end_layout

